---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="About Antonio Rodríguez Martínez"
  description="Father. Builder. Learning to be here instead of performing here."
>
  <!-- Hero Image - Full width, properly contained -->
  <div class="mb-8 animate-fade-up md:mb-12">
    <img
      src="/images/mia-y-yo-anime.avif"
      alt="Antonio Rodríguez Martínez and his daughter Mia in anime style"
      class="h-auto w-full rounded-lg object-cover shadow-lg"
      loading="eager"
    />
  </div>

  <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none space-y-3 md:space-y-4">
    <p class="animate-fade-up-delay-1 animate-fade-up">
      I'm a father, builder, and someone learning to be here instead of performing here.
    </p>

    <p class="animate-fade-up-delay-2 animate-fade-up">
      On November 6, 2025, I drew a line in the sand. I realized I'd been performing growth instead
      of living it — narrating evolution instead of embodying it. I built an identity around insight
      because it was safer than feeling. Not anymore.
    </p>

    <p class="animate-fade-up-delay-3 animate-fade-up">
      Now I'm focused on presence over productivity. Love over outrage. Clear signals over
      confusion. Integration over articulation. I curate my environment for honesty — people and
      contexts that let my nervous system heal and real connection flourish.
    </p>

    <p class="animate-fade-up-delay-4 animate-fade-up">
      I still build systems — digital, emotional, spiritual, and physical. I'm still a technical
      program manager and developer. I still run <strong>Strong Hands, Soft Heart</strong>. But
      those are roles, not identity. What I'm becoming is someone who shows up fully, who chooses
      presence over feeds, who builds a home rooted in kindness as the ultimate rebellion.
    </p>

    <p class="animate-fade-up-delay-5 animate-fade-up">
      On December 25, 2026, my son Andre Antonio was born. Mia made me a father. Andre is showing me
      I get to keep becoming one — more patient, more present, more willing to sit in the mess
      without needing to narrate it.
    </p>

    <p class="animate-fade-up-delay-6 animate-fade-up">
      These notes document the journey — raw reflections on:
    </p>

    <ul class="animate-fade-up-delay-7 animate-fade-up">
      <li>
        <strong>Integration & Growth</strong> 🧘🏽‍♂️ — moving from insight to embodiment, from performing
        to being
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Parenting</strong> 👨‍👩‍👧‍👦 — presence with my kids, the sacred in the ordinary, time as connection
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Love & Revolution</strong> 💜 — building a home rooted in kindness, love as the final
        revolution
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Clear Signals</strong> 📡 — curating honest environments, boundaries, real connection
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Politics & Culture</strong> ⚖️ — systems that serve people, dignity that doesn't need
        to be earned
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Psychology</strong> 🧠 — human behavior, healing, the body's wisdom
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Art & Expression</strong> 🎵 — creative soul, truth-telling, aesthetic power
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Systems & Strategy</strong> 💻 — digital power, code, building tools that matter
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>DIY & Creation</strong> 🛠️ — physical builds, handmade goods, crafting
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Metaspace</strong> 🌀 — reflections on the journey itself, the why and how
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="animate-fade-up-delay-8 animate-fade-up">👇 Links</h2>

    <ul class="animate-fade-up-delay-9 animate-fade-up">
      <li>
        🛠 <a href="https://builds.software" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >Builds.software</a
        > — my technical portfolio
      </li>
      <li>
        💜 <a href="https://stronghandssoftheart.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >Strong Hands, Soft Heart</a
        > — practical strength, emotional depth, sacred self-reliance
      </li>
      <li>
        🐙 <a href="https://github.com/antoniwan" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >GitHub</a
        > — open source & code
      </li>
      <li>
        🌀 <a
          href="https://bsky.app/profile/antoniwan.online"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">BlueSky</a
        > — my social brain
      </li>
      <li>
        📚 <a href="/library/books">Book library (for reference)</a> — the shelves behind these notes
      </li>
    </ul>

    <p class="animate-fade-up-delay-10 animate-fade-up">
      I've also built some <strong>meta-tools</strong> to understand my own creative patterns. The <a
        href="/brain-science"
        class="text-[rgb(var(--color-accent))] hover:underline">🧠 Brain Science</a
      > section analyzes my writing cadence, topic evolution, and intellectual journey through data visualization.
      The <a href="/tag-management" class="text-[rgb(var(--color-accent))] hover:underline"
        >🏷️ Tag Management</a
      > page provides insights into how I organize and categorize my thoughts — a window into my mental
      filing system. I've also created <a
        href="/api/"
        class="text-[rgb(var(--color-accent))] hover:underline">💬 API Documentation</a
      > with development tools including a curated collection of Stoic philosophy quotes for personal
      use and site integration.
    </p>

    <div
      class="card-alt animate-fade-up border-l-4 border-[rgb(var(--color-primary))] p-6"
      role="complementary"
      aria-label="Disclaimer"
    >
      <div class="mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
        <span class="text-xl" aria-hidden="true">🌟</span>
        <span class="font-semibold">Sacred Disclaimer</span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-body-muted m-0" style="line-height: 1.6;">
        The wisdom, practices, and digital alchemy shared here flow from personal experience and
        creative exploration. None of this constitutes medical, legal, psychological, or
        professional advice. Please consult qualified professionals for such guidance.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
